better earnings record than the soviets for the first time in 
1988 czechoslovakia joined 29 other countries where the average 
citizen earns the equivalent of more than 10000 annually the 
only country to join that group last year the figure for 
czechoslovakia was 10140 east germany was already a member with 
average earnings of 12480 last year 
at the bottom of the cias table were 45 countries from 
afghanistan to zaire where average earnings were 401 a year or 
less most of them under a dollar a day 
