<TEXT>
camcorder users filming holiday festivities should vary their 
shots using pan tilt zoom or different camera angles to keep 
the interest level high 
but dont overdo it or audiences may get dizzy cautions the 
8mm video council a new yorkbased industry trade group 
know when to stop shooting when filming childrens parties the 
organization also says though it doesnt seem long one to two 
minutes per activity is plenty and will make for better viewing 
later 
other suggestions 
keep the camera stationary and let the people create the 
action in your video 
dont backlight your subject backlighting will make your 
subjects features completely unrecognizable 
when videotaping indoors consider supplementary lights to 
accentuate color 
never aim the camcorder directly at the sun or a bright light 
or you risk causing permanent damage 
press the white balance button before shooting in a new 
setting this will automatically compensate for any discrepancies 
in lighting 
make use of your camcorders high fidelity sound capabilities 
but unless youre narrating let your subjects to do the talking 
</TEXT>
